What is the most efficient way to sort an array of integers in descending order using C++? Can you provide an example code that uses the quick sort algorithm?
Here's a sample code using the quick sort algorithm:
void quickSort(int arr[], int low, int high) {
 if (low < high) {
 int pivot = arr[high];
 int i = (low - 1);

 for (int j = low; j <= high - 1; j++) {
 if (arr[j] > pivot) {
 i++;
 swap(arr[i], arr[j]);
 }
 }
 swap(arr[i + 1], arr[high]);

 int pi = i + 1;

 quickSort(arr, low, pi - 1);
 quickSort(arr, pi + 1, high);
 }
}
To use the function, call it like this:
int arr[] = {3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9, 2, 6, 5, 3, 5};
int n = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]);
quickSort(arr, 0, n - 1);
This will sort the array in descending order.

